description:
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 - Out of Hours Volunteer Hub Co-ordinator, Voluntary Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fixed Term / Secondment (6 months) .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full Time: 37.5 Hours&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have experience in coordinating volunteers? Are you familiar with the acute hospital environment? Are you passionate about supporting volunteers to provide extra support to patients and their families during their hospital stay? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at Watford General Hospital for a Volunteer Coordinator to build upon existing volunteer services and support the Response Volunteer Hub at weekends and weekday evenings at Watford General Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will coordinate the Response Volunteers Hub to run at weekends and on Friday &amp; Monday evenings. They will also work within the Voluntary Services Team, liaising with other co-ordinators, admin staff and volunteers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate should have experience of volunteer co-ordination and administration, and needs to be available at weekends between 8am &amp; 8pm and on Mondays &amp; Fridays 12pm to 8pm. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role will be based at Watford General Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 20th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Westherts.volunteers@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
